1061
01:30:12,843 --> 01:30:17,009
The second nominee for Game of the Year,

1062
01:30:17,009 --> 01:30:19,292
Super Mario Odyssey,

1063
01:30:19,292 --> 01:30:21,095
developed by Nintendo EPD.

1064
01:30:21,095 --> 01:30:23,418
Published by Nintendo.

1065
01:30:23,418 --> 01:30:25,521
The Nintendo EPD Team.

1066
01:30:49,566 --> 01:30:53,147
Narrative in games have come a long way in a short time.

1067
01:30:53,147 --> 01:30:56,508
It wasn't that long ago that most antagonists in games

1068
01:30:56,508 --> 01:30:59,769
were two-dimensional caricatures of villains

1069
01:30:59,769 --> 01:31:03,129
devoid of motivation for all their wrongdoings.

1070
01:31:03,129 --> 01:31:06,770
Developers didn't need a reason to have a player shoot

1071
01:31:06,770 --> 01:31:08,971
thousands of rounds of ammo, chewing

1072
01:31:08,971 --> 01:31:12,372
through hundreds of digital enemies in their games.

1073
01:31:12,372 --> 01:31:14,052
But look at us now.

1074
01:31:14,052 --> 01:31:16,193
Now, games can tell moving stories.

1075
01:31:16,715 --> 01:31:20,557
deeply personal stories before sending the player off to kill their way through hours

1076
01:31:20,557 --> 01:31:21,677
of entertainment.

1077
01:31:21,677 --> 01:31:28,021
As our nominees in this category illustrate, some developers are willing to do much, much

1078
01:31:28,021 --> 01:31:28,681
more.

1079
01:31:28,681 --> 01:31:37,766
They are willing to take risks and weave tales that make us laugh, make us think, and make

1080
01:31:37,766 --> 01:31:38,166
us ask why.

1081
