1105
01:33:51,751 --> 01:33:51,891
Yeah.

1106
01:33:51,891 --> 01:33:52,111
Chelsea?

1107
01:33:52,111 --> 01:33:52,412
Yeah.

1108
01:33:52,412 --> 01:33:52,972
I just...

1109
01:33:53,973 --> 01:34:01,000
After being a part of this community for so long and seeing so many amazing things created

1110
01:34:01,000 --> 01:34:09,989
by so many amazing people, just being here is such an honor and I'm so grateful for everybody

1111
01:34:09,989 --> 01:34:11,531
who made it possible, Annapurna, Sony, and thank you.

1112
01:34:16,627 --> 01:34:18,148
Hey everyone.

1113
01:34:18,148 --> 01:34:19,970
Yeah, this was a labor of love.

1114
01:34:19,970 --> 01:34:22,072
It took everything to get this done.

1115
01:34:22,072 --> 01:34:23,433
We went through a big road of trials.

1116
01:34:23,433 --> 01:34:26,016
Special thanks to my brother who's sitting right here,

1117
01:34:26,016 --> 01:34:27,577
who was a big help on the game.

1118
01:34:27,577 --> 01:34:29,919
My girlfriend, my parents, all our families.

1119
01:34:29,919 --> 01:34:32,962
Everyone put, like, way more than themselves into this,

1120
01:34:32,962 --> 01:34:34,083
and it's fucking amazing.

1121
01:34:34,083 --> 01:34:34,744
I love you guys.

1122
01:34:52,917 --> 01:35:09,080
Here tonight to present the Ambassador of the Year Award is Poria Torkin.

1123
01:35:09,080 --> 01:35:11,841
Good evening.

1124
01:35:11,841 --> 01:35:12,801
I was born in Iran.

1125
01:35:12,801 --> 01:35:17,442
My family fled to the Netherlands when I was six years old.

1126
01:35:17,442 --> 01:35:19,522
But I was lucky.

1127
01:35:20,896 --> 01:35:25,797
Growing up Dutch provided me with incredible opportunities that many children like me never had.

1128
01:35:25,797 --> 01:35:34,719
I was incredibly fortunate to spend several years working and growing at the Peerless Guerrilla Games in Amsterdam.

1129
01:35:34,719 --> 01:35:39,460
Hermen, Angie, thank you for all the opportunities you gave me. Thank you so much.

1130
01:35:39,460 --> 01:35:43,982
And later...

1131
01:35:45,017 --> 01:35:49,258
When I applied to a studio I've wanted to work at ever since I first played Halo,

1132
01:35:49,258 --> 01:35:50,679
Bungie brought me to the United States.

1133
01:35:50,679 --> 01:35:56,681
I am lucky, and today, standing in front of a room filled with my peers,

1134
01:35:56,681 --> 01:35:59,702
I am honored to introduce my dear friend Rami.

1135
01:35:59,702 --> 01:36:09,546
Because not everyone has been as lucky as I have been.

1136
01:36:10,863 --> 01:36:15,404
It is easy to forget that there are hundreds of thousands of people across the globe

1137
01:36:15,404 --> 01:36:20,385
who would drop everything to have an internationally acclaimed game studio nearby their homes.

1138
01:36:20,385 --> 01:36:25,866
And there are hundreds of thousands of people who share the dream of standing on this stage,

1139
01:36:25,866 --> 01:36:31,567
or even simply being in this room, but who do not have the opportunities that we were granted.

1140
01:36:31,567 --> 01:36:36,367
They didn't have access to the knowledge, the jobs, the network, the press, and the visas

1141
01:36:36,367 --> 01:36:38,568
that we, and definitely I, benefited from.

1142
01:36:39,618 --> 01:36:43,819
all for reasons entirely out of their control.

1143
01:36:43,819 --> 01:36:49,921
It is because of and for these people that we are honoring Rami tonight.

1144
01:36:49,921 --> 01:37:01,125
He is not just receiving this award for his passion for independent development, his love

1145
01:37:01,125 --> 01:37:07,207
of games and the power they have to change us, or his formidable beard.

1146
01:37:09,753 --> 01:37:12,756
He is receiving this award for his accomplishments and work,

1147
01:37:12,756 --> 01:37:16,279
focused on providing people with opportunities and access

1148
01:37:16,279 --> 01:37:20,902
that each and any of us deserve, but not all of us are granted.

1149
01:37:20,902 --> 01:37:24,225
His studio, Flumbeer, has diverted significant resources

1150
01:37:24,225 --> 01:37:26,466
towards helping fellow and aspiring game developers.

1151
01:37:26,466 --> 01:37:28,728
From creating DoPressKit, a free tool which

1152
01:37:28,728 --> 01:37:32,671
is used by thousands of independent and mid-sized

1153
01:37:32,671 --> 01:37:33,632
developers around the world.

1154
01:37:39,251 --> 01:37:43,392
to working with young initiatives like Train Jam, Indie Mega Boots, or Playground.

1155
01:37:43,392 --> 01:37:48,653
From supporting and advising platforms and events with their indie offerings,

1156
01:37:48,653 --> 01:37:50,894
to organizing One Reason to Be,

1157
01:37:50,894 --> 01:37:54,735
he consistently uses his reach to raise awareness and urgency

1158
01:37:54,735 --> 01:37:58,356
on things he recognizes as unjust or underrepresented.

1159
01:37:59,647 --> 01:38:03,869
He spends a significant portion of his time traveling to emerging territories to speak

1160
01:38:03,869 --> 01:38:09,472
to students, local developers and investors, governments and accelerators, museums, universities

1161
01:38:09,472 --> 01:38:09,972
and media.

1162
01:38:09,972 --> 01:38:17,357
All with the goal to help cultivate game development communities and guide opportunities for developers

1163
01:38:17,357 --> 01:38:18,017
with potential.

1164
01:38:18,017 --> 01:38:25,341
And perhaps most notable of all, he introduced his mother to Final Fantasy and shared that

1165
01:38:25,341 --> 01:38:26,882
experience with all of us on Twitter.

1166
01:38:33,943 --> 01:38:39,834
Please join me in welcoming my friend, the man with as many names as initiatives, Rami

1167
01:38:39,834 --> 01:38:42,279
Ibrahim Mahmoud Hanafi Ismail.

1168
01:39:36,627 --> 01:39:44,194
Assalamu alaikum. My name is Rami Ismail, one half of Dutch Independent Studio of Lambeer,

1169
01:39:44,194 --> 01:39:51,400
and I'm thankful. I am thankful to my parents, who have each in their own way inspired me

1170
01:39:51,400 --> 01:39:57,125
to be driven, humble, and curious. Their presence here tonight means the world to me.

1171
01:40:06,168 --> 01:40:11,451
I'm thankful for my siblings who have instilled in me a sense of playfulness, of responsibility

1172
01:40:11,451 --> 01:40:13,212
